the US becomes more violent than the most dangerous Latin American countries. I’ll make a prediction that the US murder rate in 2030 is going to be somewhere between the highest and lowest level it’s been since the 1960s. If by that time our numbers look like Honduras or Japan instead, something important would’ve had to change.</p><p>In sum, the 2022 murder rate of El Salvador is so far outside the historical norm that it cries out for an explanation. </p><p>This leads to the second argument I’ve seen, which is that Bukele simply worked out a deal with the gangs. That case was made in a <a href="https://www.nationalreview.com/2023/03/nayib-bukele-is-no-conservative-hero/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">National Review article</a>, and <a href="https://twitter.com/mattyglesias/status/1634964273540788224" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">by Matt Yglesias</a> on Twitter. </p><figure><a href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F915b66e9-c873-4347-a26d-51039e5a2a57_836x1840.png" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/64jyyCZ50-65kQSLA_ 424w, https://reader.miniflux. 848w, https://reader.miniflux. 1272w, https://reader.miniflux. 1456w" sizes="100vw"/><img src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/tSFSDzNmblg_" alt="" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/-AE8nrS_-yf6vADE97tRVBEaXf7rCv-bA0VqbjnTisQ=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvZmV0Y2gvd180MjQsY19saW1pdCxmX2F1dG8scV9hdXRvOmdvb2QsZmxfcHJvZ3Jlc3NpdmU6c3RlZXAvaHR0cHMlM0ElMkYlMkZzdWJzdGFjay1wb3N0LW1lZGlhLnMzLmFtYXpvbmF3cy5jb20lMkZwdWJsaWMlMkZpbWFnZXMlMkY5MTViNjZlOS1jODczLTQzNDctYTI2ZC01MTAzOWU1YTJhNTdfODM2eDE4NDAucG5n 424w, https://reader.miniflux. 848w, https://reader.miniflux. 1272w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/tS